{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b951b4c0-4350-48b6-8302-633eddbc03ba","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD single-tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD multi-tenant |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Azure AD single-org auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com --tenant-id <id> --client-id <id>\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C\n\n# Minimal API with OpenAPI support (.NET 9+)\ndotnet new webapi --use-minimal-apis --auth SingleOrg\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually. Would you like help setting up a specific option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6370bb0f-cb9b-4242-91d6-9f8037bf4e71","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET development question. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of .NET templates and authentication options.\n\nThis is a general knowledge question - I don't need to search the filesystem or use tools for this. I can answer directly.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"5007:301230:3097B52:352A95D:69FBE232"},"id":"662b4f44-fc9b-450c-ab96-b5f40d330df9","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:52:11.405Z","parentId":"f5790d25-55b7-4005-8da0-f321db1d0639"}
